main event: A UFO was observed in Lanett, Alabama, on March 5, 1961, described as a silvery object traveling at high speed with no noise.
interesting points: Witness estimated the object's altitude to be around 60,000 feet., The object was about the size of a medium passenger plane., It was noted for its lack of contrail and noise, distinguishing it from an airplane., The object was seen by a private pilot, providing credibility to the observation., An orange-colored object was reported with a smaller dark orb orbiting it.
sighted object: silvery object moving at high speed
witness description: one witness was a private pilot
